Date: Fri 24 Feb 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2017; 30(09) [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=22898


Small hive beetle infestation (_Aethina tumida_), Belize
--------------------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 24 Feb 2017 from Dr Miguel Angel DePaz, Chief Veterinary Officer, Animal Health Department, Belize Agricultural Health Authority (BAHA), Central Farm, Belize

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 19 Sep 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 26 Sep 2016
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: _Aethina tumida_ Murray
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Sarteneja Area, North East Corozal, Sarteneja, Corozal
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Sep 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: apiary
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 155 / 155 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: apiaries in North East Corozal District
Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: small hive beetles were first detected in Consejo, a border coastal village. The Ministry of Agriculture conducted a survey from [23 Oct-5 Nov 2016] in Corozal, Orange Walk, and Belize Districts. 570 hives in these 3 districts were inspected and 155 hives were found infested, all in Corozal District: Consejo, Progreso, Copper Bank, and Sarteneja. Levels of infestation ranged from 2-20 beetles per colony. There was no indication that the beetles were reproducing, that is, larvae were not found.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, screening, disinfection/disinfestations, quarantine, surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, zoning, control of vectors, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: traceability

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Belize Agricultural Health Authority (BAHA) Plant Protection Laboratory (national laboratory) / Bees / entomological investigations / 23 Sep 2016 / Positive
International Regional Organisation for Plant and Animal Health (OIRSA) Headquarters Entomology (regional reference laboratory)/ Bees / entomological investigations / 23 Sep 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

